BUILD IN PROGRESS
This 36 square brick veneer home situated close to Cobram and is set on 16.4 acres of prime Cobram sandy loam ideal for vegetable or fruit growers.

The property is all set for your finishing touches, with quality built McCormack timber cabinetry in the kitchen along with large family living, formal lounge, four bedrooms all with built in robes, master with ensuite. Recommend inspection to appreciate its quality.

Description:
Rustic Country Charm
One of Cobram's original cottages full of character and rustic charm and sited on one acre of land close to the Murray River.
This property could be mistaken for being in Italy or the South of France. Think a brick open fire place, exposed ceiling beams, paved courtyard, in ground pool and undercover outdoor entertaining area, all surrounded by established trees and lawns in a peaceful rural setting. The perfect place to relax while sipping wine by the fire.
There is a house and separate bungalow, each with their own bedrooms and bathrooms. Split system air conditioning and gas heating. Also features extensive shedding, carport, and dual entry roads for easy access for trucks and machinery.
This quaint property is only 5 minutes from town and would be perfect for retirees, holiday makers or anyone looking to soak up the relaxed country lifestyle.

Description:
Four bedroom family home
This brick veneer home offers four bedrooms (three with built in robes) and two living areas. The formal lounge has gas heater and formal dining area that most people would now utilise as a study nook. The kitchen has been renovated and has dishwasher, gas stove and a good amount of storage. It overlooks the meals area and an oversized family room with built in bar and second gas heater. The family bathroom has shower, bath and vanity with a separate toilet. There is also a second bathroom off the family room which has a shower, vanity and toilet. The home has ducted evaporative air conditioning. Externally there is a fantastic outdoor entertaining area, single carport, garden shed and good sized rear yard.

Description:
Beautiful street appeal
This home is impressive from the moment you drive up the street, with its unique combination of building materials such as stonework, render and natural timbers. The home, which was built in 2007, comprises three spacious bedrooms and two living areas which all have an abundance of natural light thoughout. The galley kitchen offers 900mm wide appliances, dishwasher and overlooks the family room and separate meals area. This then extends out to the gorgeous decked outdoor entertaining area and fernery which is generous in size. The master bedroom is located to the rear of the home and has a walk in robe, well proportioned ensuite and has a sliding door out to its own small oasis. The remaining bedrooms all have built in robes. Climate throughout is controlled by gas ducted heating and evaporative cooling. The double garage has the added security benefit of having direct access into the home and also has a roller door to rear. The 6m x 8m (approx) colorbond shed will make an ideal man or she cave, with an additional toilet, trough and TV point and has its own rear yard access from the street making it ideal for the tradie. This home is sure to impress and will be the envy of all your family and friends. Make an inspection today.

Fabulous Four Bedroom Family Package!
Positioned in a quiet court on a generous 1064 square metre block, this quality family home will cater for the whole familys needs.
Features a well appointed kitchen/living area and a large second living area/lounge both with bay windows. Four generous bedrooms with built-in robes, ensuite to the main bedroom, and the main bathroom has a spa bath. Zoned ducted gas heating, evaporative cooling and ducted vacuum system.
Fantastic outdoor entertaining area - approximately 7m x 8m with ceiling fans. Spacious yard with a 10.5m x 6m colourbond shed with concrete floor and power. Lovely established surrounds, and easy vehicle access to the yard. Added bonus of 5 kilowatt solar electricity system with a 68c rebate.
A great family home with lots to offer and a must to inspect.

Description:
Immaculately presented
This stunning home is positioned in Green Palms Village and offers two living areas, three bedrooms and two bathrooms. The striking angular roofline to the front elevation has been continued internally with soaring cathedral ceilings to both living areas of the home. The large kitchen is centrally located and offers an abundance of cupboard space, island bench, gas cooktop, electric oven and single drawer dishwasher. It overlooks the meals and family area which has a natural gas log fire and opens onto a rear decked verandah. The master bedroom comprises walk in robe and ensuite with the remaining two bedrooms offering built in robes and sharing the bathroom. Externally the home has a double tandem garage with remote control access and doubles as an outdoor entertaining area and has a built in storage area/garden shed. There are also 8 solar panels, external blinds, LED lighting and double glazed tinted windows. This home is immaculately presented with quality fixtures and fittings throughout and will not disappoint.
Green Palms Village gives retirees the freedom and independence they deserve and offers storage for caravans and is conveniently located close to the public bus stop. Facilities include recreational hall and in-ground swimming pool and is located less than 3km from CBD.

Description:
Prime North Victoria Dairy operation - 266 Ha...

* Fully lasered to farm plan with a portion of automated irrigation

Full purchasing options are detailed in the memorandum
